    <item>
      <title>Install NGINX Amplify Agent</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/nginx-amplify/nginx-amplify-agent/install/installing-amplify-agent/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/nginx-amplify/nginx-amplify-agent/install/installing-amplify-agent/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;To use F5 NGINX Amplify to monitor your infrastructure, you need to install NGINX Amplify Agent on each system you wish to monitor.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;blockquote class=&#34;note&#34;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;div&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Note:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br/&gt; NGINX Amplify Agent will drop &lt;em&gt;root&lt;/em&gt; privileges on startup. It will then use the user ID of the user &lt;code&gt;nginx&lt;/code&gt; to set its effective user ID. The package install procedure will add the &lt;code&gt;nginx&lt;/code&gt; user automatically unless it&amp;rsquo;s already found in the system. If the &lt;a href=&#34;https://nginx.org/en/docs/ngx_core_module.html#user&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;user&lt;/a&gt; directive appears in the NGINX configuration, NGINX Amplify Agent will pick up the user specified in the NGINX config for its effective user ID (e.g. &lt;code&gt;www-data&lt;/code&gt;).&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;/blockquote&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;h2 &#xA;id=&#34;using-the-install-script&#34;&gt;Using the Install Script  &lt;a class=&#34;headerlink float-right&#34; href=&#34;#using-the-install-script&#34; title=&#34;Using the Install Script&#34;&gt;&lt;i class=&#34;fas fa-link fa-xs&#34;&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;Take the following steps to install NGINX Amplify Agent:&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Update NGINX Amplify Agent</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/nginx-amplify/nginx-amplify-agent/install/updating-amplify-agent/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/nginx-amplify/nginx-amplify-agent/install/updating-amplify-agent/</guid>
      <description>&lt;blockquote class=&#34;important call-out&#34;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;div&gt;&lt;strong class=&#34;call-out-type&#34;&gt;Important&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br/&gt; It is &lt;em&gt;highly&lt;/em&gt; recommended that you periodically check for updates and install the latest stable version of F5 NGINX Amplify Agent.&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;/blockquote&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;ol&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Updating NGINX Amplify Agent On Ubuntu/Debian&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;code-block&#34; data-mf=&#34;true&#34; style=&#34;display: none;&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;code-type chroma&#34;&gt;bash&lt;/span&gt;&lt;div class=&#34;code-container chroma&#34;&gt;&#xA;        &lt;button onclick=&#34;copyToClipBoard(this, &amp;#34;id-18440f1ec3fe8560&amp;#34;)&#34; class=&#34;code-copy-button multi-line&#34; type=&#34;button&#34;&gt;Copy&lt;/button&gt;&#xA;        &lt;div class=&#34;highlight-v2&#34; id=&#34;id-18440f1ec3fe8560&#34;&gt;&#xA;            &lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;apt-get update &lt;span class=&#34;o&#34;&gt;&amp;amp;&amp;amp;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;se&#34;&gt;\&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;se&#34;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;apt-get install nginx-amplify-agent&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;        &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div id=&#34;code-block-v1&#34; data-mf=&#34;false&#34;&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;apt-get update &lt;span class=&#34;o&#34;&gt;&amp;amp;&amp;amp;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;se&#34;&gt;\&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;se&#34;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;apt-get install nginx-amplify-agent&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Updating NGINX Amplify Agent On CentOS/Red Hat&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;code-block&#34; data-mf=&#34;true&#34; style=&#34;display: none;&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;code-type chroma&#34;&gt;bash&lt;/span&gt;&lt;div class=&#34;code-container chroma&#34;&gt;&#xA;        &lt;button onclick=&#34;copyToClipBoard(this, &amp;#34;id-18440f1ec4017f18&amp;#34;)&#34; class=&#34;code-copy-button multi-line&#34; type=&#34;button&#34;&gt;Copy&lt;/button&gt;&#xA;        &lt;div class=&#34;highlight-v2&#34; id=&#34;id-18440f1ec4017f18&#34;&gt;&#xA;            &lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;yum makecache &lt;span class=&#34;o&#34;&gt;&amp;amp;&amp;amp;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;se&#34;&gt;\&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;se&#34;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;yum update nginx-amplify-agent&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;        &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div id=&#34;code-block-v1&#34; data-mf=&#34;false&#34;&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;yum makecache &lt;span class=&#34;o&#34;&gt;&amp;amp;&amp;amp;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;se&#34;&gt;\&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;se&#34;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;yum update nginx-amplify-agent&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ol&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Configuring NGINX Amplify Agent</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/nginx-amplify/nginx-amplify-agent/install/configuring-amplify-agent/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/nginx-amplify/nginx-amplify-agent/install/configuring-amplify-agent/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;F5 NGINX Amplify Agent keeps its configuration in &lt;code&gt;/etc/amplify-agent/agent.conf&lt;/code&gt;. The NGINX Amplify Agent configuration is a text-based file.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 &#xA;id=&#34;overriding-the-effective-user-id&#34;&gt;Overriding the Effective User ID  &lt;a class=&#34;headerlink float-right&#34; href=&#34;#overriding-the-effective-user-id&#34; title=&#34;Overriding the Effective User ID&#34;&gt;&lt;i class=&#34;fas fa-link fa-xs&#34;&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;NGINX Amplify Agent will drop &lt;em&gt;root&lt;/em&gt; privileges on startup. By default, it will then use the user ID of the user &lt;code&gt;nginx&lt;/code&gt; to set its effective user ID. The package install procedure will add the &lt;code&gt;nginx&lt;/code&gt; user automatically unless it&amp;rsquo;s already found in the system. If the &lt;a href=&#34;http://nginx.org/en/docs/ngx_core_module.html#user&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;user&lt;/a&gt; directive appears in the NGINX configuration, NGINX Amplify Agent will pick up the user specified in the NGINX config for its effective user ID (e.g. &lt;code&gt;www-data&lt;/code&gt;).&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Uninstall NGINX Amplify Agent</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/nginx-amplify/nginx-amplify-agent/install/uninstalling-amplify-agent/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/nginx-amplify/nginx-amplify-agent/install/uninstalling-amplify-agent/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;To completely delete a previously monitored object, perform the following steps:&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h3 &#xA;id=&#34;uninstall-f5-nginx-amplify-agent&#34;&gt;Uninstall F5 NGINX Amplify Agent  &lt;a class=&#34;headerlink float-right&#34; href=&#34;#uninstall-f5-nginx-amplify-agent&#34; title=&#34;Uninstall F5 NGINX Amplify Agent&#34;&gt;&lt;i class=&#34;fas fa-link fa-xs&#34;&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;On Ubuntu/Debian use:&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;code-block&#34; data-mf=&#34;true&#34; style=&#34;display: none;&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;code-container chroma&#34;&gt;&#xA;        &lt;button onclick=&#34;copyToClipBoard(this, &amp;#34;id-18440f1ec40b8580&amp;#34;)&#34; class=&#34;code-copy-button&#34; type=&#34;button&#34;&gt;Copy&lt;/button&gt;&#xA;        &lt;div class=&#34;highlight-v2 single-line&#34; id=&#34;id-18440f1ec40b8580&#34;&gt;&#xA;            &lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;apt-get remove nginx-amplify-agent&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;        &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div id=&#34;code-block-v1&#34; data-mf=&#34;false&#34;&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;apt-get remove nginx-amplify-agent&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;On CentOS and Red Hat use:&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;code-block&#34; data-mf=&#34;true&#34; style=&#34;display: none;&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;code-container chroma&#34;&gt;&#xA;        &lt;button onclick=&#34;copyToClipBoard(this, &amp;#34;id-18440f1ec40efc38&amp;#34;)&#34; class=&#34;code-copy-button&#34; type=&#34;button&#34;&gt;Copy&lt;/button&gt;&#xA;        &lt;div class=&#34;highlight-v2 single-line&#34; id=&#34;id-18440f1ec40efc38&#34;&gt;&#xA;            &lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;yum remove nginx-amplify-agent&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;        &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div id=&#34;code-block-v1&#34; data-mf=&#34;false&#34;&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;yum remove nginx-amplify-agent&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;h3 &#xA;id=&#34;delete-objects-from-the-web-interface&#34;&gt;Delete objects from the web interface  &lt;a class=&#34;headerlink float-right&#34; href=&#34;#delete-objects-from-the-web-interface&#34; title=&#34;Delete objects from the web interface&#34;&gt;&lt;i class=&#34;fas fa-link fa-xs&#34;&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;p&gt;To delete a system using the web interface — find it in the &lt;a href=&#34;http://localhost:1313/nginx-amplify/user-interface/inventory/&#34;&gt;Inventory&lt;/a&gt;, and click on the &amp;ldquo;Trash&amp;rdquo; icon.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Use NGINX Amplify Agent with Docker</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/nginx-amplify/nginx-amplify-agent/install/using-amplify-agent-docker/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/nginx-amplify/nginx-amplify-agent/install/using-amplify-agent-docker/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;You can use F5 NGINX Amplify Agent in a Docker environment. Although it&amp;rsquo;s still work-in-progress, NGINX Amplify Agent can collect most of the metrics and send them over to the Amplify backend in either &amp;ldquo;standalone&amp;rdquo; or &amp;ldquo;aggregate&amp;rdquo; mode. The standalone mode of operation is the simplest one, with a separate &amp;ldquo;host&amp;rdquo; created for each Docker container. Alternatively, the metrics from NGINX Amplify Agents running in different containers can be aggregated on a &amp;ldquo;per-image&amp;rdquo; basis — this is the aggregate mode of deploying NGINX Amplify Agent with Docker.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
